{:proof/updated-at "2026-03-29T20:33:34.379447776Z", :proof/falsify-completed? true, :proof/cycles [{:cycle/id "apm-a01A02-C001", :cycle/blocker-id "root", :cycle/phase :completed, :cycle/phases-completed [:observe :propose :execute :validate :classify :integrate :commit :gate-review], :cycle/phase-data {:observe {:blocker-id "root", :notes "Weak L^2 estimate: m({|f|>lambda}) <= C/lambda^2 implies int_E |f| <= C_1*sqrt(m(E)). This is the layer-cake/level-set decomposition technique for interpolation."}, :propose {:approach "Layer cake: int_E |f| = int_0^inf m(E cap {|f|>lambda}) dlambda. Split at threshold lambda_0: use m(E) for small lambda, use C/lambda^2 for large lambda. Optimize lambda_0 = sqrt(C/m(E)) to get int_E |f| <= 2*sqrt(C*m(E)).", :notes "This is the standard real-variable technique. The weak-type condition m({|f|>lambda}) <= C/lambda^2 means f is in weak-L^2 (Lorentz space L^{2,inf}). The result is the embedding L^{2,inf} -> L^1(E) with the right scaling."}, :execute {:artifacts ["proof-inline"], :notes "PROOF: By the layer cake formula: int_E |f| dx = int_0^inf m(E cap {|f|>lambda}) dlambda. For any lambda_0 > 0, split: = int_0^{lambda_0} m(E cap {|f|>lambda}) dlambda + int_{lambda_0}^inf m(E cap {|f|>lambda}) dlambda. Bound (I): m(E cap {|f|>lambda}) <= m(E), so first integral <= lambda_0 * m(E). Bound (II): m(E cap {|f|>lambda}) <= m({|f|>lambda}) <= C/lambda^2, so second integral <= C * int_{lambda_0}^inf lambda^{-2} dlambda = C/lambda_0. Total: int_E |f| <= lambda_0*m(E) + C/lambda_0. Minimize: d/d(lambda_0)[lambda_0*m(E) + C/lambda_0] = m(E) - C/lambda_0^2 = 0, so lambda_0 = sqrt(C/m(E)). Substituting: int_E |f| <= sqrt(C*m(E)) + sqrt(C*m(E)) = 2*sqrt(C)*sqrt(m(E)). So C_1 = 2*sqrt(C). QED."}, :validate {:validation-artifacts ["informal-proof-complete"], :notes "Proof complete. Layer cake + optimization. All hypotheses used. The constant C_1 = 2*sqrt(C) is explicit."}, :classify {:classification :proved, :rationale "Complete proof with explicit 